reviews.review_text:
Great show, finally a good AUD tape! Out of nowhere today, I asked myself: I wonder if there is finally a decent AUD of this show, and here it is just 10 days old on the Archive! Serendipity!!

I had great floor seats and totally enjoyed this fine show. This Rosemont run was tops by 1994 standards.

The soundboard mix of this show is terrible: very flat and brash, almost no drums. SBDs are mixed for the room, and this particular room has really bad acoustics. Rosemont Horizon was perhaps the worst sounding venue I’ve ever been to. Getting a decent AUD would require being FOB.  

This AUD captures the drums and mix much better than the SBD. Yeah there is crowd noise, but the music is all there.

Thanks for posting this after all these years!
